World Freedom Day is a commemoration of the fall of the Berlin Wall on November 9, 1989. It celebrates the end of division and oppression and the reunification of Germany. The day serves as a reminder that the work of freedom is ongoing and calls for reflection on how to promote liberty and protect human dignity. It also highlights the interconnectedness of the world and the potential to build bridges between people. The proclamation emphasizes the responsibility of nations that have secured freedoms to support democracy and the rule of law in other countries. President Barack Obama calls upon the people of the United States to observe World Freedom Day and reaffirm their dedication to freedom and democracy.